 sctk, I think the design is quite modern, minimalist and doesn't commit too much to one platforms style. \r\n\r\nI've asked for the designer's permission before implementing these decorations and he seems happy to help sctk by providing use of his design, hopefully this will fix a few issues about the 'ugly' decorations provided by BasicFrame, especially considering gnomes firm resistance to server side decorations in wayland.\r\n\r\n'ConceptFrame' is just a place holder title until jman6495 responds about what his design is called or otherwise we could maybe name it something generic like 'BGRTabbedFrame' or 'MinimalistFrame', etc.", "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/39/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/39/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null, "score": 1.0}, {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/38", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/38/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/38/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Smithay/client-toolkit/issues/38/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/Smithay/client-toolkit/pull/38", "id": 365763344, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0MjE5NjAxODY4", "number": 38, "title": "Cleanup - Handle function errors, remove unnecessary assignment, pass arguments more efficiently", "user": {"login": "trimental", "id": 40879396, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjQwODc5Mzk2", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/40879396?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/trimental", "html_url": "https://github.com/trimental", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/trimenta